.TH "t4_get_link_params" 9 "t4_get_link_params" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
t4_get_link_params \- retrieve basic link parameters for given port
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" t4_get_link_params
.BI "(struct port_info *pi "  ","
.BI "unsigned int *link_okp "  ","
.BI "unsigned int *speedp "  ","
.BI "unsigned int *mtup "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "pi" 12
the port
.IP "link_okp" 12
value return pointer for link up/down
.IP "speedp" 12
value return pointer for speed (Mb/s)
.IP "mtup" 12
value return pointer for mtu

Retrieves basic link parameters for a port: link up/down, speed (Mb/s),
and MTU for a specified port.  A negative error is returned on
failure; 0 on success.
